snippet: Lieutenant Kerchner, as an Army Ranger, led his company up the face of a towering cliff to seize German big guns overlooking the American invasion beaches of D-Day.
abstract: George Kerchner, former Army Ranger who led a D-Day maneuver, dies at age 93.
